# Byz Notation Webapp Project

## Overview
a browser-based educational application for **absolute beginner music students** using the **Byzantine Greek paralage (solfege) system**.

## Tech Stack
- Language: Typescript (if a backend language is needed, prefer Golang)
- Key frameworks: React
- Infrastructure: Local workstation for now - Linux/Mac compatible

## Coding Standards
- Follow eslint linting standards
- All functions must include docstrings/comments
- Error handling: Always include proper try-catch with context
- Logging: Use structured logging with appropriate levels

## Testing
- Write unit tests for all new features
- Minimum 80% code coverage
- Integration tests for API endpoints

## Project Structure
- `/src` - Main application code
- `/tests` - Test files
- `/docs` - Documentation
- `/config` - Configuration files

## Specific Preferences
- Use async/await for I/O operations
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Always validate input at API boundaries
- Include metrics/observability in new features

